        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 8 at 8:16PM EST by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 813 PM EST, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms with
heavy rainfall along a line extending from near Plyler to Indian
Trail. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Albemarle, Troy, Badin Lake, Biscoe, Plyler, Fairview In Union
County, Locust, Norwood, Badin, and Oakboro.

This includes Interstate 73 between Mile Markers 38 and 42, and
between Mile Markers 47 and 51.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead to
localized minor flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
